The paper deals with performance metrics and analysis of wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses channel gains and fading, which are related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of the uncertainty cube and spatial contention to categorize and analyze different types of wireless networks involves mathematical analysis (cs.MA) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also discusses the comparison of different performance metrics, which can be seen as a data science problem (cs.DS).
